FuncDef:
The aaa offline-record mib-order lexicographical-order command configures the device to display user offline records in the MIB table hwAAAOfflineRecordTable in lexicographical order.
The undo aaa offline-record mib-order lexicographical-order command cancels the configuration.
By default, the display of user offline records in the hwAAAOfflineRecordTable is based on the offline time, starting from the record containing the latest offline time.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
By default, the data of each node in the MIB table hwAAAOfflineRecordTable containing user offline records is displayed based on the user offline time, with the record containing the latest offline time being displayed first. To display the data of each node in lexicographical order from A to Z, run the aaa offline-record mib-order lexicographical-order command.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
